Wow! A very heavily orchestrated arrangement of Kathy's Waltz. Not quite sure how I feel about it. It's beautiful, but I'm not sure if it falls under Brubeck's simplistic, cool jazz style.
It might be time to change the From The Album notification, Last fm.
certainly not from Time Out, but cool nonetheless!  never heard this version with violins ablaze in the background......
His jazz sound really was  and would stay exceptional for ever !!
Y el gran Paul Desmond siempre ahí...
motuweth2 is correct - this version is from "The Essential Dave Brubeck" album, the version on this album ("Time Out") is a simpler version, sans orchestra. Both versions are wonderful!
But is there another version without the orchestra? I'm sure my old vinyl (same artwork as here) had a more earthy version with just the quartet...
I always love hearing this piece.
